      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Determine the coordinates of the point at the tail of <m>\vec{v}=\langle 3,7 \rangle</m> if the head of <m>\vec{v}</m> is drawn at the point <m>(-2,3)</m>.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <sidebyside widths="47% 47%" margins="0%">

            <p>
              As illustrated in <xref ref="trigonometry-vectors-exercises-figure-3-solution">Figure</xref>, if we let <m>\vec{u}=\langle x_1,y_1 \rangle</m> where <m>(x_1,y_1)</m> is the point at the tail of <m>\vec{v}</m>, then <m>\vec{u}</m> is the solution to the equation <m>\vec{u}+\vec{v}=\langle -2,3 \rangle</m>.  Let's solve for <m>\vec{u}</m>.
              <md>
                <mrow>\vec{u}+\vec{v}\amp=\langle -2,3 \rangle</mrow>
                <mrow>\vec{u}\amp=\langle -2,3 \rangle-\vec{v}</mrow>
                <mrow>\vec{u}\amp=\langle -2,3 \rangle-\langle 6,-5 \rangle</mrow>
                <mrow>\vec{u}\amp=\langle -2-3,3-7 \rangle</mrow>
                <mrow>\vec{u}\amp=\langle -5,-4 \rangle</mrow>
              </md>
              The point at the tail of <m>\vec{v}</m> is <m>(-5,-4)</m>.
            </p>

            <figure xml:id="trigonometry-vectors-exercises-figure-3-solution">
              <caption>Determine the Point at the Tail of <m>\vec{v}</m></caption>
              <image>
                <description>
                  A vector labeled <m>\vec(u)</m> draw from the origin to the point <m>(-5,-4)</m>, a vector labeled <m>\vec{v}</m> is drawn from the point <m>(-5,-4)</m> to the point <m>(-2,3)</m>, and an unlabeled vector is drawn from the origin to the point <m>(-2,3)</m>.   
                </description>
                <latex-image>
                  <![CDATA[
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                      \begin{axis} [axis equal image,
                                    xmin=-8,xmax=4,
                                    ymin=-8,ymax=4,
                                    xtick={-6,-4,-2,2},
                                    ytick={-6,-4,-2,2},
                                    minor xtick={-7,-5,-3,-1,1,3,5,7},
                                    minor ytick={-7,-5,-3,-1,1,3,5,7}]
                        \addplot[soliddot,color=black] coordinates {(-5,-4)} node[below] {$(x_1,y_1)$};
                        \addplot[interval,ultra thick,red!30!blue,-{Stealth}] coordinates {(0,0) (-2,3)};
                        \addplot[interval,ultra thick,blue,-{Stealth}] coordinates {(-5,-4) (-2,3)} node[pos=0.65,above left] {$\vec{v}$}; 
                        \addplot[interval,ultra thick,red,-{Stealth}] coordinates {(0,0) (-5,-4)} node[pos=0.5,below right] {$\vec{u}$}; 
                      \end{axis}
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                  ]]>
                </latex-image>
              </image>
            </figure>

          </sidebyside>
        </solution>
